    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-11-08T00:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-11-08T00:35:00-05:00" n="583"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d583">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.51A/888: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ford</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-11-08T09:00:00+03:25"
                            >November 8, 1943—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 11:46 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1051. In three sessions Majlis has passed only 6 out of more than 20 articles of
                    income tax bill. Millspaugh considers progress too slow and says that if it is
                    not finally passed at tomorrow’s session the Mission will stop work the
                    following day. Believing Majlis will ultimately pass bill rather than have
                    Mission leave, he attributes delays to a desire to test his determination to
                    resign. Accordingly, he proposes to make no further extensions of resignation
                    date and thinks if the Mission ceases to function it will convince the Majlis he
                    means business and will result in quick action on the bill.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Ford</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
